It's important to keep in mind user comfort and safety when working with raw data noise since it can often result in very loud or unpleasant sounds. It's advisable to start at a low volume and allow users control over the playback volume and the option to stop the sound immediately if needed.

Remember that this is largely an artistic or exploratory endeavor—the "patterns" you might perceive in the noise are a result of how the binary data incidentally aligns with audible frequencies, rather than an intentional encoding of sound.

